      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation domain (FDA generic pump geometry, operating envelope) overlaps sufficiently with COU domain (Class II CPB device, clinical operating range) to support extrapolation at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The FDA generic centrifugal pump shares key geometric features (volute, impeller blade count, shroud clearance) with the subject device. The five validation operating points span the clinical CPB flow range (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds representative of commercial CPB pumps. Validation-to-COU domain overlap assessed as adequate for MRL 2 without full geometric identity."
