    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. Quantitative validation against FDA interlaboratory experimental data demonstrates NIH prediction accuracy within the pre-specified ±20% acceptance band across all five operating points, with RH < 1 at all conditions. The computational model is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the COU decision of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
